            <fr:title text="Contrapositive of the pumping lemma">Contrapositive of the <fr:link href="jms-018N.xml" title="The pumping lemma for regular languages" addr="jms-018N" type="local">pumping lemma</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-016M.xml" title="Formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">formal language</fr:link> such that for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ell \geq  1]]></fr:tex>, there exists some <fr:link href="jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">string</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w\in  L]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \lvert w\right \rvert \mathclose {}}\geq  l]]></fr:tex> such that for any decomposition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w=u_1 v u_2]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \lvert u_1v\right \rvert \mathclose {}}\leq  \ell ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v]]></fr:tex> non-empty, there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_1 v^n u_2]]></fr:tex> lies outside <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is not <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7776</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6117</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6117.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>This is precisely the contrapositive of <fr:link href="jms-018N.xml" title="The pumping lemma for regular languages" addr="jms-018N" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-018N" /></fr:link>.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
